slit /slɪt/

(slitting,slits) 

1. V-T If you slit something, you make a long narrow cut in it. 切开; 撕开 

例： They say somebody slit her throat. 他们说有人割断了她的喉咙。 

例： He began to slit open each envelope. 他开始撕开每个信封。 

2. N-COUNT A slit is a long narrow cut. 狭长的切口 

例： Make a slit in the stem about half an inch long. 在树干上割一个约半英寸长的口儿。 

3. N-COUNT A slit is a long narrow opening in something. 裂缝; 缝隙 

例： She watched them through a slit in the curtains. 她透过窗帘的缝隙注视着他们。

